ve - to explore empirical data. Outlining the implications of the research for practice and service development, the book will be of interest to policy makers and practitioners in the field of domestic violence, especially those who provide services for sexual minorities, as well as students and academics interested in issues of domestic and interpersonal violence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aFamily violence. 0aSame-sex partner abuse. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Violence in Society.2bisacsh1 aHester, Marianne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311119634340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447307457zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447307457/original  a978-3-11-119634-3 Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA